As the year comes to a close I can’t help but to reflect back on my life . If I were to speak to my 9yr old self she would probably be in disbelief . 
She would be surprised that in spite of all the negativity, bullying, and over all quality of living that I kept my word to her …. 
I promised her we wouldn’t end up like everyone else and that one day we will succeed in whatever we set out to do , in the same token she wouldn’t be all that surprised because as a kid I just knew I could do it , my childhood self was very determined and self assured and I honestly had to relearn her level of confidence and determination, Today I am so happy that I stuck by my morals and never did anything that made me feel uncomfortable or made me question what is right or wrong . 
As for my goals they are becoming a reality ….I have no intentions of slowing down I’m just getting started . Thanks 2022 for all of the new people and new experiences and especially the new mindset …😎I’m ready for you 2023 #worlddomination

I have been hearing negative comments about my body for as long as I can remember…”you’re too thin “  or “you probably don’t eat “ .

I also receive unsolicited advice about my appearance…”wait till you turn 25 your metabolism will slow down and you will finally look like a woman “ or “don’t you want to be slim thick men don’t like bones” ….to be honest I don’t give a crap about your opinions or unsolicited advice…as a 30yr old WOMAN it has taken me my entire life to be comfortable with who I am and how I look ..

I couldn’t care less if my appearance makes you uncomfortable…. However I do agree that Health is important and being extremely small or extremely large are both detrimental to your health. I have been skinny my whole life since I was a toddler and I also enjoy living an active life style . At the end of the day this is who I am so please feel free to keep your unwarranted opinions to yourselves or understand that if you dish it out be ready to take it ! 💪🏾
